          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
</font></div>
        </div>
      </div><br>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">ARTICLE
II</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">DEFINITIONS</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">For
the purposes of this Plan, the following words and phrases shall have the
meanings indicated, unless the context clearly indicates otherwise:</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.1&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Affiliated
Company</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Affiliated Company&#8221; means the Company and each other
corporation or enterprise, which as of a given date, is then a member of the
same controlled group of corporations or the same group of trades or businesses
under common control, determined in accordance with Sections&#160;414(b) and (c)
of the Code, as is the Company.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.2&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Aggregated
Plans</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Aggregated Plans&#8221; means the Advance Auto Parts, Inc.
Deferred Compensation Plan, and any other account balance form of deferred
compensation plan allowing elective deferrals that is sponsored by an Affiliated
Company, and which&#160;&#160;is required to be aggregated with this Plan
pursuant to IRS Regulation &#167;1.409A-1(c)(2).</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.3&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Base
Salary</font>.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      &#8220;Base Salary&#8221; of an Eligible Executive for a Plan Year means the base rate
      of cash compensation otherwise payable by an Employer to or for the
      benefit of the Eligible Executive for services rendered or labor performed
      while that Eligible Executive is a Participant in this Plan for such Plan
      Year, including the base pay that an Eligible Executive could have
      received in cash in lieu of:</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(i)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Compensation
      deferrals elected to be made under this Plan or the Advance Auto
      Parts,&#160;Inc. Deferred Compensation Plan, or under any other
      non-qualified deferred compensation plan maintained by the Company or
      other Affiliated Company; and</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
        <div>
          <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
              <tr valign="top">
                <td style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                  <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
                </td>
                <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                  <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(ii)</font></div>
                </td>
                <td>
                  <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">      </font>
                    <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Contributions
      made by or on the Eligible Executive&#8217;s behalf to any qualified retirement
      plan, or to any Code Section&#160;125 cafeteria plan or other employee
      benefit plan maintained by the Company or other Affiliated
      Company.</font></div>
                  </div>
                </td>
              </tr>
          </table>
        </div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Any
      compensation paid to an Eligible Executive after the last day of a Plan
      Year solely for services performed during the final payroll period (as
      described in Code Section&#160;3401(b)) containing the last day of the
      Plan Year shall be treated as compensation for services performed in the
      subsequent Plan Year.&#160;&#160;For example, if a payroll period begins
      on December&#160;23 of Year 1 and ends on January&#160;5 of Year 2, then
      the compensation for that payroll period shall be treated as Year 2
      compensation.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.4&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Beneficiary</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Beneficiary&#8221;
means the person, persons or entity designated by the Participant or by the
terms of the Plan to receive any benefits payable under the Plan pursuant to
Article&#160;VII.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.5&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Board</font>.&#160;&#160;Except
as provided in Section&#160;6.1, &#8220;Board&#8221; means the Board of Directors of the
Company as constituted from time to time.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">2</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: lightgrey" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.6&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Board
Service Period</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Board Service Period&#8221; means, with respect to
a Director, the period beginning on the date of each annual meeting of the Board
(or, in the case of a newly-elected Director, beginning on the first day of the
Director&#8217;s membership on the Board) and ending on the date immediately preceding
the following annual meeting of the Board, or such other designated annual
period of service as a member of the Board.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.7&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Code</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Code&#8221;
shall mean the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended.&#160;&#160;References
to any provision of the Code or regulation (including a proposed regulation)
thereunder shall include any successor provisions or regulations.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.8&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Company</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Company&#8221;
means Advance Auto Parts,&#160;Inc., its successors, and any organization into
which or with which Advance Auto Parts,&#160;Inc. may merge or consolidate or to
which all or substantially all of its assets may be transferred.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.9&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Compensation
Committee</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Compensation Committee&#8221; means the Compensation
Committee of the Board, or any successor to such committee.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.10&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Deferral
Election Agreement</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Deferral Election Agreement&#8221; (sometimes
referred to simply as a &#8220;Deferral Election&#8221;) means the agreement governing an
Eligible Individual&#8217;s deferral of the receipt of Eligible Compensation as
submitted by the Eligible Individual under the Plan in accordance with
Section&#160;3.3.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.11&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Deferral
Period</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Deferral Period&#8221; means the period defined in
Section&#160;3.5.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.12&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Deferred
Amount</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Deferred Amount&#8221; means the amount defined in
Section&#160;3.4.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.13&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Deferred
Stock Unit or DSU</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Deferred Stock Unit&#8221; or &#8220;DSU&#8221; shall mean a
bookkeeping entry that represents the right to receive one Share at a future
date.&#160;&#160;To the extent the Company pays a dividend, DSUs will include
the right to receive Dividend Equivalents, which are credited in the form of
additional DSUs.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.14&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Deferred
Stock Unit Account or DSU Account</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Deferred Stock Unit
Account&#8221; or &#8220;DSU Account&#8221; means an account in which Deferred Amounts are valued
as if they were invested in Company stock.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.15&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Director</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Director&#8221;
shall mean a member of the Board.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.16&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Disabled</font>.&#160;&#160;A
Participant shall be considered to be or have become &#8220;Disabled&#8221; for purposes of
the Plan if, by reason of any medically determinable physical or mental
impairment which can be expected to result in death or can be expected to last
for a continuous period of not less than twelve&#160;months, the
Participant:</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Is
      unable to engage in any substantial gainful activity;
  or</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Is
      receiving, and has received for a period of not less than three months,
      income replacement benefits under another accident and health plan
      covering employees of the Participant&#8217;s
  Employer.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">3</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: lightgrey" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">A
Participant will be deemed to be Disabled if the Participant has been determined
to be disabled (i)&#160;by the Social Security Administration, or
(ii)&#160;under a disability insurance program having a definition of disability
that satisfies the standard prescribed above.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.17&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Dividend
Equivalents</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Dividend Equivalents&#8221; shall mean an amount equal
to the regular cash dividends paid by the Company upon one Share.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.18&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Eligible
Compensation</font>.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      &#8220;Eligible Compensation&#8221; of any Eligible Executive for any period means the
      Base Salary, Quarterly Bonus or Roll-up Performance Bonus, if any,
      otherwise payable to the Eligible Executive for services performed during
      such period.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      &#8220;Eligible Compensation&#8221; of a Director for any period means the Retainer,
      or portion thereof, payable to the Director for services performed during
      such period.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.19&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Eligible
Executive</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Eligible Executive&#8221; means an Employee of an
Employer who with respect to the Plan Year at issue:</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Holds
      a position with the Company, or an Affiliated Company, of a Senior Vice
      President, or a position senior to, or recognized as being equivalent to,
      a Senior Vice President; and</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Satisfies
      any such other eligibility requirements as the Compensation Committee may
      establish from time to time.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.20&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Eligible
Individual</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Eligible Individual&#8221; for a Plan Year means a
Director or Eligible Executive who is eligible to participate in the Plan for
that Plan Year.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.21&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Employee</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Employee&#8221;
shall mean any employee of the Company or any Affiliated Company.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.22&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Employer</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Employer&#8221;
means each Affiliated Company having Employees who are eligible to participate
in the Plan.&#160;&#160;An Affiliated Company qualifying as an Employer as of
January&#160;1, 2005 shall continue as such, subject to the provisions of the
Plan.&#160;&#160;For periods on and after January&#160;1, 2005, if an Affiliated
Company acquires a corporation or other trade or business, and if the acquired
entity is thereupon maintained as a separate Employer or operating unit with
respect an Affiliated Company in general, then such entity shall not be deemed
to be an Employer with respect to the Plan, and the Employees employed by that
entity shall not be eligible to participate in the Plan, unless and until the
Company directly, or acting through the Plan Administration Committee,
affirmatively designates the acquired entity as an Employer.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.23&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">ERISA</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;ERISA&#8221;
means the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974, as
amended.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.24&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Participant</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Participant&#8221;
means a Director or an Eligible Executive who has elected to participant in the
Plan by filing a Deferral Election Agreement as provided in
Article&#160;III.&#160;&#160;Each Director who is awarded Shares Grants shall
also be a Participant with respect to such awards.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">4</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: lightgrey" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.25&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Plan</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Plan&#8221;
means this Deferred Stock Unit Plan for Non-Employee Directors and Selected
Executives, as may be amended from time to time.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.26&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Plan
Administration Committee</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Plan Administration Committee&#8221;
means the committee that is responsible for the operation and administration of
the Plan, as identified in Section&#160;8.1(c).</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.27&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Plan
Year</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Plan Year&#8221; means a 12-month period beginning January 1
and ending the following December&#160;31.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.28&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Qualified
Change in Control Event</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Qualified Change in Control Event&#8221;
is a change in control of an Employer, as more fully prescribed in
Article&#160;VI.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.29&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Quarterly
Bonus</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Quarterly Bonus&#8221; means the amount awarded to an
Eligible Executive for each quarterly performance period within a Plan Year
pursuant to any approved incentive plan maintained by an Employer.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.30&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Retainer</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Retainer&#8221;
means any retainers payable to a Director for services performed for the Board
during a Board Service Period, exclusive of any supplemental Board meeting fees,
chair fees or committee meeting fees payable to the Director.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.31&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Retirement</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Retirement&#8221;
or &#8220;Retired&#8221; means:</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">In
      the case of a Participant who is an Eligible Executive, the Participant&#8217;s
      Separation from Service after both attaining age&#160;55 and completing at
      least 10 continuous years of service with the Affiliated Companies;
      and</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
        <div>
          <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
              <tr valign="top">
                <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                  <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
                </td>
                <td>
                  <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">      </font>
                    <div align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">In
      the case of a Participant who is a Director, the Participant&#8217;s Separation
      from Service.</font></div>
                  </div>
                </td>
              </tr>
          </table>
        </div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.32&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Roll-up
Performance Bonus</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Roll-up Performance Bonus&#8221; means the bonus
of the same name that is awarded to an Eligible Executive under an incentive
plan maintained by an Employer.&#160;&#160;Under the terms of the incentive
plan, a Roll-up Performance Bonus is (i) contingent upon the satisfaction of
organizational or individual performance criteria, and (ii) measured on the
basis of a performance period of 12&#160;months (being the Plan
Year).&#160;&#160;A performance bonus payable to an Eligible Executive that does
not satisfy both of the above conditions will be treated under the Plan as a
Quarterly Bonus.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.33&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Separation
from Service</font>.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">In
      the case of a Participant who is a Director, a Separation from Service
      will occur when the Director ceases to be a member of the Board; provided
      that (i) the cessation constitutes a good-faith and complete termination
      of the Director&#8217;s service relationship with the Company, and (ii)&#160;it
      is not anticipated that the services of the Director will be renewed,
      either as a Director, or as an independent contractor or an Employee of
      the Company or another Affiliated
Company.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Subject
      to the further provisions of this Section&#160;2.33, a Participant who is
      an Eligible Executive will incur a Separation from Service for purposes of
      the Plan if the Eligible Executive dies, retires, or otherwise has a
      termination of employment as to all the&#160;&#160;Affiliated
      Companies.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">5</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: lightgrey" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(c)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">An
      Eligible Executive&#8217;s employment relationship with an Affiliated Company
      will be treated as continuing intact, and thus the Eligible Executive will
      not be deemed to have incurred a Separation from Service, while the
      Eligible Executive is on military leave, sick leave or other bona fide
      leave of absence if the period of such leave does not exceed
      six&#160;months, or if longer, so long as the Eligible Executive retains a
      right to reemployment with the Affiliated Company under an applicable
      statute or by contract.&#160;&#160;A leave of absence constitutes a bona
      fide leave of absence only if there is a reasonable expectation that the
      Eligible Executive will return to perform services for the Affiliated
      Company.&#160;&#160;If the period of leave exceeds six&#160;months and the
      Eligible Executive does not retain a right to reemployment under an
      applicable statute or by contract, the employment relationship is deemed
      to terminate on the first day immediately following such six-month
      period.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(d)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Whether
      a termination of employment has occurred is determined based on whether
      the facts and circumstances indicate that the Affiliated Company and the
      Eligible Executive reasonably anticipated that no further services would
      be performed after a certain date, or that the level of bona fide services
      the Eligible Executive would perform after such date (whether as an
      Employee or as an independent contractor) would permanently decrease to no
      more than 20 percent of the average level of bona fide services
      performed&#160;&#160;(whether as an Employee or an independent contractor)
      over the immediately preceding 36-month period (or the full period of
      services to the Affiliated Companies if the Eligible Executive has been
      providing services to the Affiliated Companies less than 36
      months).&#160;&#160;An Eligible Executive is presumed to have incurred a
      Separation from Service where the level of bona fide services performed
      decreases to a level equal to 20 percent or less of the average level of
      services performed by the Eligible Executive during the immediately
      preceding 36-month period.&#160;&#160;An Eligible Executive will be
      presumed not to have incurred a Separation from Service where the level of
      bona fide services performed continues at a level that is 50 percent or
      more of the average level of service performed by the Eligible Executive
      during the immediately preceding 36-month period.&#160;&#160;No
      presumption applies to a decrease in the level of bona fide services
      performed to a level that is more than 20 percent, and less than 50
      percent, of the average level of bona fide services performed during the
      immediately preceding 36-month
period.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.34&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Share</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Share&#8221;
shall mean a share of common stock of the Company, par value $.0001 per
share.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.35&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Shares
Grant</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Shares Grant&#8221; means the grant of Shares, if any,
awarded by the Company to a Director as authorized by the Company&#8217;s 2004
Long-Term Incentive Plan (&#8220;2004 LTIP&#8221;).</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.36&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Specified
Employee</font>.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Each
      Participant who is an Eligible Executive, or an Employee serving as a
      Director, shall be deemed to be a Specified Employee for purposes of the
      Plan, and therefore shall be subject to distribution restrictions
      prescribed under Section&#160;5.6 of the
Plan.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">A
      Participant who is not an Eligible Executive, or an Employee serving as a
      Director, (i.e.,&#160;an &#8220;outside&#8221; Director) is not a Specified Employee,
      and therefore is not a Specified Employee for purposes of the
      Plan.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">6</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: lightgrey" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
2.37&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Specified
Time</font>.&#160;&#160;&#8220;Specified Time&#8221; means a designated Deferral Period with
respect to a DSU Account that based on a stated number of years, as prescribed
in Section&#160;3.5(b).</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
</font></div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">7</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: lightgrey" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; COLOR: #000000; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
</font></div>
        </div>
      </div><br>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">ARTICLE
III</font></font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">PARTICIPATION
AND DEFERRAL ELECTIONS</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
3.1&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Eligibility</font>.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Each
      Director and Eligible Executive who was a Participant in the Plan as of
      December&#160;31, 2007 shall continue as such, subject to the provisions
      of the Plan.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">On
      or after January&#160;1, 2008, each individual who becomes a Director or
      an Eligible Executive shall be immediately eligible to become a
      Participant in the Plan.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(c)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">An
      Eligible Executive who is transferred from an Employer to employment with
      an Affiliated Company that is not an Employer with respect to the Plan, or
      who while continuing in the employ of an Employer ceases to be an Eligible
      Executive (a &#8220;Transferred Participant&#8221;), shall not be considered to have
      incurred a Separation from Service.&#160;&#160;The Transferred Participant
      shall continue to be eligible to make deferrals under the Plan through the
      end of the Plan Year in which such transfer occurs, or for such additional
      period as may be permitted by the Compensation
  Committee.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
3.2&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Duration
of Participation</font>.&#160;&#160;Each Participant shall remain a Participant
under the Plan until the balance of all of the Participant&#8217;s DSU Accounts has
been distributed to the Participant or the Participant&#8217;s
Beneficiary.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
3.3&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Deferral
Election Agreement</font>.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">For
      each Board Service Period, each Director shall be permitted to submit a
      Deferral Election Agreement with respect to the Retainer otherwise payable
      to the Director for services performed during the Board Service
      Period.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">For
      each Plan Year, each Eligible Executive for that Plan Year shall be
      permitted to submit a separate Deferral Election Agreement with respect to
      each of the forms of Eligible Compensation otherwise payable to the
      Eligible Executive for services performed during the Plan
      Year.&#160;&#160;The forms of Eligible Compensation for a Plan Year
      consist of Base Salary, Quarterly Bonuses and Roll-up Performance
      Bonus.&#160;&#160;For administrative convenience, the Plan Administration
      Committee can direct that the elections for two or more forms of the
      Eligible Compensation be combined on a single form.&#160;&#160;The
      submission of the Deferral Election Agreement must be made in accordance
      with such policies and procedures established by the Plan Administration
      Committee and communicated to Eligible Individuals, which procedures may
      permit or require elections to be made by electronic
  media.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(c)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      Deferral Election Agreement with respect to each form of Eligible
      Compensation shall include the elections and descriptions prescribed
      below.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
        <div id="FTR">
          <div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div>
        </div>
        <div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">8</font></div>
          <div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center">
            <hr style="COLOR: lightgrey" noshade size="2">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="HDR">
          <div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 108pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(i)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      amount of the Participant&#8217;s Eligible Compensation to be deferred for the
      Board Service Period or Plan Year, as applicable
      (i.e.,&#160;the&#160;&#8220;Deferred Amount,&#8221; as described more fully in
      Section&#160;3.4);</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 108pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(ii)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      designated payment event for such Deferred Amount, as described more fully
      in Section&#160;3.5; and</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td align="right" style="WIDTH: 108pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(iii)&#160;&#160;</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      form in which the Deferred Amount is elected to be paid, as described more
      fully in Section&#160;3.6.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
3.4&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Deferred
Amount</font>.</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      Deferral Election Agreement of a Participant for a Board Service Period or
      Plan Year, as applicable, shall designate the amount of each form of the
      Eligible Compensation for the period that the Participant elects to have
      deferred under the Plan (the&#160;&#8220;Deferred
  Amount&#8221;).</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(i)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">A
      Director may elect to defer up to 100% of his or her Retainer for a Board
      Service Period.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 72pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(ii)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">An
      Eligible Executive shall make a separate deferral election for each form
      of the Eligible Executive&#8217;s Eligible Compensation (i.e.,&#160;Base Salary,
      Quarterly Bonus and Roll-up Performance Bonus) for the Plan
      Year.&#160;&#160;The maximum or minimum amount of deferral that may be
      elected by an Eligible Executive for a Plan Year with respect to each form
      of Eligible Compensation shall be established by the Plan Administration
      Committee.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div>
        <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
            <tr valign="top">
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
              </td>
              <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)</font></div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      aspect of a Deferral Election Agreement regarding the elected Deferred
      Amount shall not apply to any pay period for which the amount of the
      Eligible Compensation remaining to be paid to the Participant (but for the
      deferral election), after making any other deductions or withholdings of
      income, would be less than the Deferred Amount prescribed in the Deferral
      Election Agreement.</font></div>
              </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Section
3.5&#160; <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: normal; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Designated
Payment Event</font>.&#160;&#160;A Participant&#8217;s Deferral Election Agreement
must designate the event that will give rise to the payment of the Deferred
Amount.&#160;&#160;The period of the deferral through the date of the event
giving rise to the payment of the Deferred Amount is sometimes referred to
herein as the &#8220;Deferral Period.&#8221;&#160;&#160;Subject to the terms of the Plan,
including Section&#160;5.6 (regarding the restriction on distributions to
Specified Employees), a Participant may elect to have the Deferred Amount
pertaining to services performed in any Board Service Period or Plan Year, as
applicable, become payable upon either of the following alternative
events:</font></div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
        <div>
          <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
              <tr valign="top">
                <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                  <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
                </td>
                <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                  <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(a)</font></div>
                </td>
                <td>
                  <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">      </font>
                    <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      Participant&#8217;s Retirement or other Separation from Service;
      or</font></div>
                  </div>
                </td>
              </tr>
          </table>
        </div>
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">
          <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
          <div>
            <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
                <tr valign="top">
                  <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                    <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
                  </td>
                  <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                    <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(b)</font></div>
                  </td>
                  <td>
                    <div align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">      </font>
                      <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">The
      last day of a future calendar year; provided, however, that such
      designated calendar year cannot be earlier than the second calendar year
      following the calendar year in which falls the first day of the Board
      Service Period or Plan Year, as applicable, to which the deferred
      compensation pertains (i.e.,&#160;as of a &#8220;Specified
      Time&#8221;).&#160;&#160;For example, a Director may elect the designated
      payment event for a DSU Account pertaining to the Board
      </font></div>
                    </div>
                  </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
      <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">
        <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">
          <div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>
          <div>
            <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="hangingindent" width="100%">
                <tr valign="top">
                  <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                    <div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;
      </font></div>
                  </td>
                  <td style="WIDTH: 36pt">
                    <div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">&#160;</div>
